visual.name: smartFilterByOKViz
visual.description: Smart Filter by OKViz works like an observer, showing the current filters set in the report page, or like a slicer, allowing you to choose records from a drop-down list or search by typing a few letters.

author.name: OKViz - a trademark of OKViz corp.

bookmarks.description: Upgrade to the Pro version of this visual to use Power BI bookmarks.

sync.description: Upgrade to Pro version of this visual to sync slicers.

incremental.description: Upgrade to the Pro version of this visual to retrieve all data items, bypassing the limit of 30K records.

pasting.description: Upgrade to the Pro version of this visual to unlock copy & paste feature. You will able to choose also how to split multiple strings, pasted from applications such as Excel.

autocomplete.description: Upgrade to the Pro version of this visual to use the autocomplete inline feature (it works like the Chrome search bar).

themes.description: Upgrade to the Pro version of this visual to support themes.

observerInteraction.description: Upgrade to the Pro version of this visual to enable user interaction in Observer mode.

customization.description: Upgrade to the Pro version of this visual to get additional customization options such as font family, dropdown background color, and more. See the Appearance section for all available settings.

alertsEdit.description: Show alerts when you try to use a feature available only in the Pro version of this visual (in Edit mode only)

alertsView.description: Show alerts when you try to use a feature available only in the Pro version of this visual (in View mode only)

mode.description: Select the operational mode of the visual.

maxResults.description: Select how many items to include in the auto-complete dropdown list displayed when user types in the input box.

maxSelection.description: Select how many items can be selected from the dropdown list.

maxObserved.description: Select how many items to display in the Observer list. Max 1000.

showObservedCount.description: When the number of observed items is greater than the max allowed, show the count of hidden items.

singleSelection.description: Allow only one item to be selected at the same time.

compressMultiple.description: When multiple items are selected, reduce the space reserved for keywords.

filterMultiple.description: When multiple fields are connected, each selection box filters the other ones.
